$interpreted: Panther Chieftain: I object! She's not one of us—she doesn't have our interests at heart. Isn't that Insect Princess proof enough of that?
Panther Chieftain: Lord Juan-Yun treated her so well. Anybody could see that. But see how she repaid his kindness...
Juan-Yun: ...When I came around, I was astonished, too... I never thought Princess Tindoiimu could be capable of such a thing...
Wolf Chieftain: True! She saw how the young Lord was reborn under Udumbara. Dissatisfaction wasn't enough for her—she had to destroy Udumbara,
Wolf Chieftain: call forth these monsters, and she even attempted to kill him when he tried to stop her... Fortunately he had the Holy Dragon's protection on his side and was able to escape.
Toyokuni: ......
Shun: Hmph, I've never trusted those shady insects!
Soohyeon: She's shouldering a debt of blood, after all...
Turtle Chieftain: Don't we have a debt of blood to be paid by the Bewitchers? How many of us have they killed!?
Soohyeon: They aren't bewitching people on purpose!
Soohyeon: Like I told you, Li Hwa and the others have discovered the key already. With a little more time, they'd be able to find a way to cure the Bewitchers...
Panther Chieftain: It's not certain that they'd succeed, though, is it?
Soohyeon: Oof...
Soohyeon: (Why now, of all times...)
Toyokuni: ...Soohyeon? Are you feeling unwell?
Soohyeon: No, I'm fine!
Soohyeon: (I can't fail, not now. I've got to persuade them... The Bewitchers are depending on me. Pull yourself together, Soohyeon!)
Soohyeon: They will succeed! I believe in Li Hwa! With enough people and resources—
Wolf Chieftain: —And what if they don't?
Soohyeon: Gyah...
Wolf Chieftain: Sounds to me like you Bewitchers want to drag the rest of us to your graves with you.
Soohyeon: Th-that's not true!
Soohyeon: (Waah...! It's getting bad!)
Panther Chieftain: The East is facing an existential threat, a matter of life and death. Even with all our resources going to fighting the monsters, it's still not enough.
Panther Chieftain: Not only would you have us give up the fight, you'd take everything we've got and gamble it on a miracle cure only you believe in?
Shun: What!? Absolutely not! I object, too!
Soohyeon: (I... can't take it...)
Soohyeon: No, I...
Toyokuni: The risks are too great... This is truly ill-advised, Soohyeon.
Soohyeon: No... ngh... Please, everybody... just listen...
Juan-Yun: Soohyeon? Are you...
Turtle Chieftain: I say we shouldn't let the Bewitchers go. Let's wipe them out as soon as we can, and solve this once and for all!
Soohyeon: ...Why does it always turn out like this...
Juan-Yun: Soohyeon? Just relax...
Soohyeon: Why... Why!! We belong to the East, too! Don't we count?
Yonghyeon: Soohyeon!?
Yonghyeon: Was that you shouting? What's going on!?
Soohyeon: Why do you always resort to violence, without a moment's reflection!? If that's how it's gonna be, I'll kill you all first!!
Yonghyeon: Kong Soohyeon, calm yourself!
Li Hwa: She's lost her mind. It looks like her condition is worsening—we'll have to stop her before we can treat her!
Yonghyeon: Tch... I'm coming!
Soohyeon: I just want to keep everyone safe! They're people too!!
Yonghyeon: Kong Soohyeon! Calm down!
Soohyeon: Let me go! I'm trying... to help...!!
Soohyeon: *sob*...!
Li Hwa: Pull yourself together, Soohyeon!
Li Hwa: If you lose it here and someone gets hurt, the Bewitchers will have lost their only hope!
Soohyeon: ...Could I... hurt anyone...?
Soohyeon: *sob*...
Li Hwa: Yes! You have to prove that the Bewitchers are capable of controlling themselves!
Soohyeon: I...
Soohyeon: *sob*... Waaah...
Soohyeon: ...I would never, I just... I just...
Soohyeon: ...*sob*... I...
Soohyeon: ...I...
Yonghyeon: ...Have you come back to your senses?
Soohyeon: Yes... Yonghyeon, Li Hwa, I... I'm sorry, I've ruined everything...
Yonghyeon: Hey...!
Li Hwa: It must have taken all her strength to pull herself back to rationality. Let's get her back to Pearl Manor right away!
